Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportAlwaysOnBuffer(25.10)                        reportAlwaysOnBuffer(25.10)

Name
       reportAlwaysOnBuffer  - Reports the available always-on buffers and in-
       verters per domain

Syntax
       reportAlwaysOnBuffer

       [-help]

       [-all]

       [-powerDomain <domainName>]

       [-verbose]

       Reports the available always-on buffers and inverters per domain.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each  reportAlwaysOnBuffer  parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:  man reportAlwaysOnBuffer.

       -all   Reports the always-on buffers and inverters for all domains.  If
              you  specify  no  parameter,  even then it reports the always-on
              buffers and inverters for all domains.

       -powerDomain <domainName>
              Reports the always-on buffers and inverters  for  the  specified
              domain.

              Note: Parameters -all and -powerDomain are mutually exclusive.

       -verbose
              Reports the possible reason why a domain does not have always-on
              buffers  and  inverters.  It  can also report the always-on cell
              list per domain if the always-on cells are available for the do-
              main.

Examples
              * The following command displays  all  the  available  always-on
                buffers and inverters for each power domain.

                reportAlwaysOnBuffer

                Always on buffers found for each power domain:

                      PowerDomain  "TDSPCore"  (pd  tag = "1") has 1 always on
                buffer(s) to use

                      PowerDomain "PLL"  (pd  tag  =  "2")  has  1  always  on
                buffer(s) to use

                      PowerDomain  "AO"  (pd  tag  =  "3")  has  1  always  on
                buffer(s) to use

              * The following command reports the always-on  buffers  and  in-
                verters for the PD1 domain:

                reportAlwaysOnBuffer -powerDomain PD1

                The software displays the following message:

                PowerDomain  "PD1" (pd tag = "1") has 2 always on buffer(s) to
                use

